@article{cuello2001bonding,
   abstract={The crystallography of the Ω phase and its relation with the body centered cubic (bcc) phase was reviewed. The Ω and bcc phases can be described by an hexagonal lattice with three atoms per unit cell. The bonding-induced atomic ordering (BIAO) hypothesis using very accurate neutron diffraction was examined. Neutron diffraction for Ti-V alloys indicate that dB-Bdecreases smoothly with the V additions in the range where the ideal Ω phase forms. In Zr-Nb alloys, the dB-Bdistance shows a complex variation with the Nb content.},
