   year={2004},
}
@article{Marinelli2000,
   abstract={This paper is the first of a series presenting the results of a systematic experimental study of the lattice parameters (LPs) of the metastable phases formed by quenching Fe-Mn alloys with 0 to 30 at% Mn Here the LPs of the face-centered cubic (γ) and body-centered cubic (α') phases are investigated as functions of composition, using an X-ray technique A rather detailed discussion of the experimental methods is presented In particular, the use of a plastic deformation treatment for stabilising the α' phase relatively to the γ phase is described With the present data, trends are established in the composition dependence of the LPs and the average volumes per atom of the γ and α' phases, which are used in assessing the relative volume change associated with the γ → α' martensitic transformation (orig)},
