@article{Troiani1998a,
   abstract={Abstract ?-phase Cu-48at% Zn single-crystal slices with (100)? and (110)p surface orientations have been dezincified in vacuum at 450 and 600°C for various times, and the resulting surfaces have been studied by optical microscopy, and also by scanning and transmission electron microscopy. On dezincification, the ? phase becomes unstable and two different competing nucleation processes occur, one being a coherent homogeneous nucleation within the ?-phase matrix of a non-equilibrium 4H type of hexagonal structure, and the other a heterogeneous formation of long straight needles of the fcc α phase, with an interface orientation given by (211)? parallel to (121)α and a parallelism of the close packed directions [011]? and [111]α within the planes. ?-phase Cu-48at% Zn single-crystal slices with (100)? and (110)p surface orientations have been dezincified in vacuum at 450 and 600°C for various times, and the resulting surfaces have been studied by optical microscopy, and also by scanning and transmission electron microscopy. On dezincification, the ? phase becomes unstable and two different competing nucleation processes occur, one being a coherent homogeneous nucleation within the ?-phase matrix of a non-equilibrium 4H type of hexagonal structure, and the other a heterogeneous formation of long straight needles of the fcc α phase, with an interface orientation given by (211)? parallel to (121)α and a parallelism of the close packed directions [011]? and [111]α within the planes.},
