@article{Isalgue1994,
   abstract={The presence of precipitates in SMA influences strongly their properties. We present some experimental results for small γ phase precipitates (around 10 nm) in Cu-Zn-Al single crystals. The shift in transformation temperatures and the evolutive behaviour of the stress/temperature width on cycling are interpreted as due to the creation of dislocations and to the subsequent plastic deformation of martensite around the precipitates as a consequence of the β-martensite interface passing through the material. With the appropriated thermomechanical treatment, the precipitate growth could be oriented to give a symmetry breakdown of the system and, as a result, a two way shape memory effect could be obtained.},
