@article{Isalgue1994,
   abstract={The rigorous constancy of the transformation temperatures and the steadiness of the local behaviour of the material seem hard to achieve in SMA. This is the reason for evaluating the causes that generate the evolution of the material and estimating the evolutive parameters. The analysis has been done in Cu-Zn-Al single crystals of nominal Ms ⋍ 288 K. A secular evolution can be observed from the initial thermal treatment. The main effects are: a) characteristic effects of the number of plates of martensite and of the frictional processes; b) local evolutions of Ms caused by the presence of the interfaces parent to martensite; c) dynamic actions of cooperative type for the groups of plates. The observations also suggest the rearranging of the plates associated to the perturbations of the external fields.},
