   abstract={We consider a model for O ordering in which any two O ions of the CuOχ planes repel each other with a screened Coulomb repulsion, but the repulsion energy between two second-neighbor O ions with a Cu ion in between is reduced by ΔE, to account for the stabilization energy of perfect chains due to covalency and charge transfer. We calculate the screening length λ using Thomas-Fermi theory, a slave-boson treatment of correlations and experimental data. For reasonable values of ΔE, the ground state of the model is consistent with most of the observed diffraction data, with a possible explanation of photoinduced effects for χ ∼ 0.4, and with recent calculations relating Tc with χ.},
