@inproceedings{Amengual1992a,
   abstract={The use of Cu--Zn--Al single crystals (electronic concentration e /a=1.48) and of high resolution equipment allows study of the evolution of one or a few martensite domains. This kind of study proves the existence of intrinsic thermoelasticity, the differences between different friction processes (interface movements and nucleation) and also the coherence of the hysteresis loops obtained through mechanical stress or temperature. The different evolutions linked to the creation of dislocations or to the change of gamma precipitates can …},
