@article{FernandezGuillermet1991b,
   abstract={The thermodynamic properties of the Zr-Nb system are poorly known from direct measurements, and there is a lack of information on the Gibbs of its various stable phases, which is necessary in thermodynamic modelling of ternary and higher-order phase diagrams based on Zr-Nb That kind of information has been obtained by us Our approach involves the analysis and synthesis of selected pieces of experimental phase-equilibrium data using models for the Gibbs energy of bcc, hcp and liquid, and the evaluation of a set of optimum model parameters The present thermodynamic description is used to construct, by calculation, a phase diagram for the Zr-Nb system, which is confronted with experiments of various types We also compare our results on the thermodynamic behavior of the individual phases with estimates from Miedema's method, and other predictive approaches (orig)},
