   abstract={A transmission electron microscopy study of β and martensite phases of CuAlMn shape memory alloys has been performed. For this purpose, four different alloys were prepared —Cu-9.8A1-4.4Mn, Cu-10.8A1-4.2Mn, Cu-11.1A1-5.4Mn, Cu-113A1-6.1Mn. The influence of the heat treatment on the β(L21) phase order is important. The martensite structure is closely dependent on the electron concentration (e/a), being 2H for an e/a greater than 1.45, while for values below this, it presents an 18R structure.},
