@article{Tolley1989,
   abstract={In this paper, results are reported on 18R to 2H transformations in 18R single variant crystals which are obtained in two different ways, by compression and by thermal cycling under constant load. A detailed crystallographic analysis of the transformation is made. Defects in the resulting 2H structure are studied by TEM. By comparing with the previously reported results of this transformation in Cu-Zn-Al and Cu-Al-Ni alloys, it is concluded that two different 2H variants can be obtained from 18R single variant crystals, each having an undistorted habit plane with the matrix. The stability of the 2H phase with respect to 18R is discussed. © 1989.},
