@article{Guillermet1989b,
   abstract={Recent evaluations of the thermodynamic properties and the phase diagram of the Co-C and the Co-W system, based on the Hillert-Jarl model for magnetic Gibbs energy, predict an effect of C and W on the Curie temperature of fcc Co which is smaller than according to the magnetic measurements compiled by Hansen and Anderko The conflict is considered in the present paper in the light of more recent experimental information We show that recent thermogravimetric determinations of Tc in Co-W alloys, and measurements on ternary alloys along the Co-WC section of the Co-W-C system, support the predictions from thermodynamic data We emphasize, however, that accurate experimental data for clarifying the conflict between predictions and the early magnetic data on the Co-C fcc solutions are still lacking (orig)},
