   abstract={The acoustic emission (AE) generated during the martensitic transformation (MT) of Cu--Zn--Al alloys has been studied. It has been shown that just after a quench from T sub q , the AE shows a maximum for T sub q approx=850K. However, if the measurements are done after a beta -phase ageing (t=45 ks, T sub a=290K), the AE does not present any marked dependence on T sub q . The AE is therefore influenced by the quenched-in vacancies. Based on this result, a method is proposed for studying vacancy elimination kinetics from AE …},
