@article{Sade1988,
   abstract={Mechanical and thermal fatigue has been investigated with Cu-Zn-base alloys of different transformation temperatures. Microscopic methods were combined with tensile and compressive loading, especially under pseudoelastic conditions. The relevance of properties measured with single crystals for polycrystalline alloys was tested by microscopic observation of the behavior of grain boundaries and their environments. The results indicate that the behavior of single crystals is similar to that of polycrystals unless the grain boundaries are embrittled in the high temperature phase β. For fatigue in the martensitic state, several intra-martensitic crack nucleation mechanisms provide conditions for which no considerable differences occur between single and polycrystals. Models for the intra-crystalline mechanisms of fatigue under cyclic pseudoelastic loading conditions have been proposed.},
