@article{Guillermet1988a,
   abstract={The Fe-Co-W phase diagram has been constructed by using the CALPHAD method. The thermodynamic properties of the solid phases are predicted by combining the contributions from the binary sistems Co-Fe, Co-W and Fe-W according to the Redlich-Kister phenomenological model, whereas a ternary excess Gibbs energy parameter is evaluated for the liquid phase. Various types of sections of the phase diagram are reported. In particular, sections illustrating the magnetic effects, which are treated by means of the Hillert-Jarl model, are reported. Comparisons between calculations and early experiments and recent microprobe measurements are presented. The comparisons give the impression of a general compatibility between experiments and calculations, although some discrepancies are observed. The need of more experimental work on the Fe-Co-W system is emphasized.},
   author={Armando Guillermet},
